Recommend this get moved to a helper utility, maybe in `src/utils/automerge/automerge.ts` or in its own `getMissionDocHandle.ts`

```
export async function getMissionDocHandle(missionId: number): Promise<DocHandle<Mission>> {
  const url = missionIdToUrl.get(missionId)
    ?? (await getAutomergeDocListing([missionId]))[0]?.automergeUrl as AutomergeUrl;
  if (!url) throw new Error(`No Automerge document found for mission ID ${missionId}`);
  const handle = await globalValues.automergeRepo.find(url);
  await handle.whenReady();
  return handle;
}

// Map populated at server startup and whenever a new mission is created
const missionIdToUrl = new Map<number, AutomergeUrl>();
export function cacheMissionUrl(missionId: number, url: AutomergeUrl) {
  missionIdToUrl.set(missionId, url);
}
```

`cacheMissionUrl` would be called in the existing startup loop in `server.ts` and in `createAutomergeMission` for new missions. The selected block here then becomes:

```
const handle = await getMissionDocHandle(rexEva.missionId);
if (handle.doc()?.landerLocation) egressLocation = handle.doc().landerLocation;
```

Just using `rexOverwrite` as an example, but anywhere the current pattern is used server-side to get docHandles would use this new pattern.

When there is more than just "mission" in automerge, the missionIdToUrl would become something like

```
type MissionDocUrls = {
  mission: AutomergeUrl;
  actions?: AutomergeUrl;
  evas?: AutomergeUrl;
};
const docUrlsByMissionId = new Map<number, MissionDocUrls>();
```

Looking at all of the use of this where it's a two-stage "get the url from redux" then "pass the url into useDocSelector", I was wondering if you like the idea of making a wrapper for each doc like

```
export function useMissionDocSelector<TSel>(
  selector: (doc: Mission) => TSel,
  isEqual: EqualityFn<TSel> = Object.is
): TSel | undefined {
  const automergeUrl = useAppSelector((state) => state.mission.automergeUrl, refEqual);
  return useDocSelector<Mission, TSel>(automergeUrl as AutomergeUrl, selector, isEqual);
}
```

This would let us have
`const missionName = useMissionSelector((doc) => doc.name, refEqual);`
in each component
